The CIX RTS5453 driver only builds its suspend/resume/restore callbacks when
CONFIG_PM_SLEEP is enabled, while its dev_pm_ops table is declared
unconditionally. Builds without CONFIG_PM_SLEEP therefore fail because the PM
table references undeclared callback identifiers.

Keep the existing CIX table layout, but resolve those callback initializers to
NULL when sleep PM is disabled.

Link: https://github.com/cixtech/cix-linux-main/issues/14
---
diff --git a/drivers/usb/typec/rts5453.c b/drivers/usb/typec/rts5453.c
--- a/drivers/usb/typec/rts5453.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/typec/rts5453.c
@@ -760,6 +760,10 @@ static int rts5453h_restore(struct device *dev)
 
 	return ret;
 }
+#else
+#define rts5453h_suspend	NULL
+#define rts5453h_resume	NULL
+#define rts5453h_restore	NULL
 #endif
 
 static void rts5453h_shutdown(struct i2c_client *client)
